The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem in a metric space, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of uncertain data and the focus on expected cost also suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The study of probabilities and realizations also suggests a connection to stochastic processes and information theory, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory) categories.
